body:
Some memoryview (and other internal) names seem to have slipped in the list of names that star-imports compared against, that I doubt were intended (or anticipated). This PR changes the lists to something more reasonable and helpful.

This PR also takes the opportunity to unify the mapping code of the assignments/rejection name lists by using Python strings for everything, which we probably have or need anyway, thus avoiding additional C string storage for them.

The `memslice.pyx` test currently allows assignments to these names (in the master branch):

<details>

```python
['PyExc_IndexError',
 'PyExc_ValueError',
 'Py_None',
 '__pyx_collections_abc_Sequence',
 '__pyx_memoryview_thread_locks',
 '__pyx_memoryview_thread_locks_used',
 'contiguous',
 'generic',
 'global_A',
 'global_B',
 'indirect',
 'indirect_contiguous',
 'strided']
```
</details>

commit.message:
Rewrite import-star name matching to avoid lengthy chains of if-elif comparisons.
